{"topicSections":[{"title":"Percent-Encoding Sets","identifiers":["doc:\/\/com.karwa.WebURL\/documentation\/WebURL\/PercentEncodeSet","doc:\/\/com.karwa.WebURL\/documentation\/WebURL\/PercentEncodeSet\/urlComponentSet","doc:\/\/com.karwa.WebURL\/documentation\/WebURL\/PercentEncodeSet\/formEncoding"]},{"title":"Encoding and Decoding Lazily","identifiers":["doc:\/\/com.karwa.WebURL\/documentation\/WebURL\/LazilyPercentEncoded","doc:\/\/com.karwa.WebURL\/documentation\/WebURL\/LazilyPercentDecoded","doc:\/\/com.karwa.WebURL\/documentation\/WebURL\/LazilyPercentDecodedWithSubstitutions"]}],"seeAlsoSections":[{"generated":true,"title":"Creating or Modifying URLs","identifiers":["doc:\/\/com.karwa.WebURL\/documentation\/WebURL\/WebURL"]}],"metadata":{"modules":[{"name":"WebURL"}],"title":"Percent-Encoding and Decoding","role":"collectionGroup"},"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"content","content":[{"text":"What is Percent-Encoding?","type":"heading","anchor":"What-is-Percent-Encoding","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Because URLs are a string format, certain characters may have special meaning depending on their position:"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"for example, a "},{"code":"\"\/\"","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" in the path is used to separate the pathâ€™s segments, and the first "},{"code":"\"?\"","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" in the URL"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"marks the start of the query section. This poses an interesting question:"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"What if I have a path component that contains a "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"text":"literal","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":" forward-slash?"}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["\"https:\/\/example.com\/music\/bands\/AC\/DC\" ","\/\/                                 ^","\/\/            \"AC\/DC\" should be a single component!"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"When these situations occur, we need to encode (or â€œescapeâ€) the slash in our path component,","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"so it wonâ€™t be confused with the path delimiters. URLs use a form of encoding called "},{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"percent-encoding"}]},{"type":"text","text":","},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"because it encodes binary data using "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"\"%XX\""},{"type":"text","text":" strings, where "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"XX"},{"type":"text","text":" is a hexadecimal byte value."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"For the ASCII forward-slash character, the byte value is ","type":"text"},{"code":"2F","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":", so the URL shown above would become:","type":"text"}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["\"https:\/\/example.com\/music\/bands\/AC%2FDC\"","\/\/                                 ^^^ ðŸ˜Œ"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Percent-encoding is particularly important when building strings for URL components at runtime, because it means that"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"even "},{"code":"\"\/\"","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" or "},{"code":"\"?\"","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" characters in user input wonâ€™t be confused with path delimiters or other characters with special"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"meaning to the URL. Additionally, since percent-encoding always produces an ASCII string, we can use it"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"to encode Unicode text in URLs."}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["func urlForProfile(_ username: String) -> WebURL {","  var url  = WebURL(\"https:\/\/example.com\/\")!  ","  url.path = \"\/accounts\/\" + username.percentEncoded(using: .urlComponentSet) + \"\/profile\"","  return url","}","","urlForProfile(\"BakerAli88\") ","\/\/ âœ… \"https:\/\/example.com\/accounts\/BakerAli88\/profile\"","urlForProfile(\"AC\/DC??\")","\/\/ âœ… \"https:\/\/example.com\/accounts\/AC%2FDC%3F%3F\/profile\"                             ","\/\/                                  ^^^^^^^^^^^^^","urlForProfile(\"GÃ¼nther\")    ","\/\/ âœ… \"https:\/\/example.com\/accounts\/G%C3%BCnther\/profile\"                            ","\/\/                                  ^^^^^^^^^^^^","urlForProfile(\"ðŸ¦†\")","\/\/ âœ… \"https:\/\/example.com\/accounts\/%F0%9F%A6%86\/profile\"","\/\/                                  ^^^^^^^^^^^^"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Since URL components are percent-encoded, their contents must be recovered by decoding."}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["let url = WebURL(\"https:\/\/%F0%9F%A6%86@example.com\/\")!","url.username                  \/\/ \"%F0%9F%A6%86\" - Who's that?","url.username.percentDecoded() \/\/ \"ðŸ¦†\" - Oh..."]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Remember - percent encoding exists so that URL components have an unambiguous structure."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"If you decode a componentâ€™s value too early or too many times, you may introduce bugs."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"The following example demonstrates this with two approaches to split a path string in to its components."}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["let url = urlForBand(\"AC\/DC\") ","\/\/ \"https:\/\/example.com\/bands\/AC%2FDC\"                              ","\/\/                     ^^^^^^^^^^^^^^","","\/\/ The Right Way: Split, then decode each component.","let rawPath = url.path \/\/ \"\/bands\/AC%2FDC\"","let rawPathComponents = rawPath.split(\"\/\").map { $0.percentDecoded() }","\/\/ âœ… [\"bands\", \"AC\/DC\"]","","\/\/ The Wrong Way: Decode the entire path, then split.","let decodedPath = url.path.percentDecoded() \/\/ \"\/bands\/AC\/DC\"","let decodedPathComponents = decodedPath.split(\"\/\")","\/\/ âŒ [\"bands\", \"AC\", \"DC\"]"]},{"style":"tip","type":"aside","name":"Tip","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":""},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Working with percent-encoded path strings can be tricky. We recommend leaving it to the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/com.karwa.WebURL\/documentation\/WebURL\/WebURL\/pathComponents-swift.property"},{"type":"text","text":" view wherever possible."}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Data is encoded using a ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/com.karwa.WebURL\/documentation\/WebURL\/PercentEncodeSet"},{"text":" that informs the encoder which characters are allowed","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"in the resulting string. The URL Standard defines some encode-sets, and you can define your own.","type":"text"}]},{"text":"Extensions to Standard Library Types","type":"heading","anchor":"Extensions-to-Standard-Library-Types","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"WebURL provides a number of extensions to standard library types to aid"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"in encoding or decoding percent-encoded data."}]},{"text":"Encoding Text or Binary Data","type":"heading","anchor":"Encoding-Text-or-Binary-Data","level":3},{"items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"String.percentEncoded(using: PercentEncodeSet) -> String"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"code":"Collection.percentEncodedString(using: PercentEncodeSet) -> String","type":"codeVoice"}]}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"To percent-encode a String, call the "},{"code":".percentEncoded(using:)","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" function and specify an encode-set to use."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/com.karwa.WebURL\/documentation\/WebURL\/PercentEncodeSet\/urlComponentSet","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" is usually a good choice for arbitrary strings:"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"it includes all URL special characters, and encodes some additional characters to match the JavaScript function"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"code":"encodeURIComponent","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"If you have binary data, you can call the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":".percentEncodedString(using:)"},{"type":"text","text":" function, which is available"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"on all collections of bytes, to produce a percent-encoded ASCII string of its contents."}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["\"AC\/DC\".percentEncoded(using: .urlComponentSet)","\/\/ \"AC%2FDC\"","Data(...).percentEncodedString(using: .urlComponentSet)","\/\/ \"%BAt_%E0%11%22...\""]},{"text":"Decoding Strings to Text or Binary Data","type":"heading","anchor":"Decoding-Strings-to-Text-or-Binary-Data","level":3},{"items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"code":"String.percentDecoded() -> String","type":"codeVoice"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"String.percentDecodedBytesArray() -> [UInt8]"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"To decode a String containing percent-encoding, call the "},{"code":".percentDecoded()","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" function, which decodes the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"string to bytes and interprets them as Unicode text. If the decoded bytes do not contain Unicode text,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"call "},{"code":".percentDecodedBytesArray()","t